                  <handDesc>
                     <p>There is an upper margin of 3.5 cm in fragment b. The hand is a large, slightly rounded uncial, not very neat but regular, datable to the third century A.D. There are no diacritical marks, but the text has been corrected by the same hand. The text appears on the recto across the fibers and was written before the private letter on the back, also written across the fibers.</p>
